headline: Danaher Q4 Earnings Beat Estimates, Life Sciences Sales Up Y/Y
summary: DHR beats Q4 estimates as sales rise 4.5%, driven by strength across Life Sciences, Diagnostics and Biotech, and issued upbeat 2026 earnings guidance.

headline: 3M’s Mixed Q4 Beat and Softer Outlook Could Be A Game Changer For 3M (MMM)
summary: 3M Company recently reported its fourth-quarter and full-year 2025 results, with quarterly sales rising to US$6,133 million while net income and earnings per share from continuing operations declined compared with the prior year. Despite this mixed financial picture, 3M’s ongoing restructuring under CEO Bill Brown and new patent licensing with Credo Technology Group highlight efforts to improve operations and strengthen its technology portfolio. headline: 1 Industrials Stock to Keep an Eye On and 2 We Brush Off
summary: Even if they go mostly unnoticed, industrial businesses are the backbone of our country. But their prominence also brings high exposure to the ups and downs of economic cycles. Luckily, the tide is turning in their favor as the industry’s 17.2% return over the past six months has topped the S&P 500 by 8.4 percentage points.
